I will continue to use my voice in Congress to call for strong international recognition of the facts of the Armenian Genocide and to celebrate the strength and tenacity of the Armenian diaspora here in the San Fernando Valley, and around the world.
The U.S. government has a moral obligation to the victims of this genocide to speak the truth, and we cannot yield to pressure from Turkey and allow that truth to be distorted.
This Congress, I was proud to be an original cosponsor of the Armenian Genocide resolution recognizing and condemning the genocide.

As we remember the victims, we must honor their memory by advocating greater understanding, education and acknowledgement of this crime, and by pushing back on attempts to trivialize it through mischaracterization or denial.
Today marks the 104th anniversary of the beginning of the Armenian Genocide, an atrocity during which 1.5 million ethnic Armenians were murdered by the Ottoman Empire.
